\title{Fourier Basis}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{
  In the [Hilbert Space](FA-000U) #{ L^2 (\mathbb{T} ) } with the [inner product](FA-002M)
  ##{
    \left\langle f,g \right\rangle = \int _\mathbb{T} \overline{f(x)}g(x)dx
  }
  the Fourier basis elements are the functions
  ##{
    e_{n} (x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{ 2 \pi }}e^{inx}
  }
}